title: It's a Trap
description: Lex Luthor plays a deadly game of "know thine enemy," baiting Superman into a remote hideout in search of a kidnapped woman named Brie Gruyere. The super hero pounds Lex through the ceiling of another building housing the victim, where the "girl" turns out to be a Kryptonite gas spewing robot. As Superman and Lex ponder aloud the predictability of a foe's actions, it looks like Lex, armed with a Kryptonite club, is winning. But he may not know his enemy as well as he thinks.

title: Dendy
description: KO and Dendy watch some clouds.

title: Water
description: Drink up this song by Apple and Onion (If you're thirsty and want a song drink).

title: Sticky Clarence
description: Everything Clarence comes into contact with sticks to his body - a pen, a can of beans, even one of his chickens! Eventually, Clarence becomes the center of a big ball of objects.

title: Adventure Academy: Weather or Naught
description: In a lesson on how to control a Weather Gnome, Witchy Simone casts a spell that causes a blizzard and Prohyas must tame the weather with Magiswords.

title: Lonely Lonnie
description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo record themselves telling scary stories in the treehouse.

title: How to Draw Grey Matter
description: Ben 10 character designer, Chap Yaep, shows you how to draw Grey Matter.

title: Sleep
description: Apple and Onion show you how to get a good nights, pure, 100% sleep.

title: Steven Reacts
description: Steven reacts live to a brand new episode of his favorite cartoon show.

title: Good Cop, Bat Cop
description: Deadshot's been enlisted to put a hit on Batman but with Superman's help they thwart his plan and take him into custody. Stuck in a barren interrogation room, Superman offers to play bad cop for a change but he's such a decent guy that Deadshot just laughs at him. Batman's attempt at playing good cop though seems to make an impression on the villainous creep, and definitely not a good one.

title: Synth Buttons
description: Mordecai and Rigby realize that the bridge of the ship is also a synthesizer.

title: Life of Darrell
description: Lord Boxman explains where all the robots that constantly attack the Plaza come from.

title: How to Draw Robin
description: Teen Titans Go! character designer Chris Battle shows you how to draw Robin.

title: Here Piggy Piggy
description: Uncle Grandpa chases his pig through the classic opening title sequence.

title: Power Outage
description: It's Wonder Woman's first day of Flyer's Ed and her chance to prove to Red Tornado, the instructor, what a great flyer she is. But her lap through the aerial obstacle course is fraught with disaster when Cheetah takes control of Wonder Woman's flight safety belt.

title: Need for Speed
description: The Flash is running wild in Metropolis! Lena Luthor has strapped a confusion inducing Blue Kryptomite to his back and now he's running so fast that he's shaking the foundations of Metropolis. It's up to the girls at Super Hero High; Batgirl, Wonder Woman, Supergirl and Bumblebee, to stop The Flash in his tracks and save Metropolis!

title: Diamondhead AW1: Great Petropian Civil War Part 1
description: Petropia is a planet as breathtaking and indestructible as its crystalline inhabitants, the Petropians. Occupied by many factions, a civil war broke out between the Petropians and the war-like Subsapiens from below. Little did they know, a third faction, the Antrosapians, awaited with far more sinister intentions for the kingdom.

title: Uncle Grandpa 101
description: Uncle Grandpa teaches a classroom of Uncle Grandpas how to be Uncle Grandpa.

title: Magiswords 101: Electrifying Swords
description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some of the most electric.

title: Pool Fools Special
description: Tired of their local public swimming pool, the Warriors travel to the Dinosaur Kingdom. Includes special bonus vlogs.

title: Let's Do It Together
description: A special video showcasing the evolution of OK K.O.!

title: Steven Song Time
description: Steven teaches you how to play a new song he wrote!

title: Time Loop
description: Mordecai and Rigby get stuck in a space-time loop.

title: Enid's Bad Day
description: Enid is pushed to the limit by her job.

title: Hero of the Month: Supergirl
description: Supergirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Clarencio Magnifico
description: Clarence performs a magic act for some of Aberdale's senior citizens.

title: How to Draw Blossom
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Blossom.

title: How to Draw Blossom
description: The Powerpuff Girls character designer, Cheyenne Curtis, show you how to draw Blossom.

title: Bakugan: Beyond the Brawl - Battle for the Joystick
description: Drago and Hydorous Brawl to see who will play the next video game, but wind up destroying Dan's controller and coffee table.

title: Bakugan: Behind the Battle - Artulean
description: Dan introduces us Lightning's Bakugan Partner Artulean, letting us know what makes his abilities so special.

title: Bakugan: Beyond the Brawl - Playground Showdown
description: The Magnus Bakugan engage in a no rules game of "Capture the Flag."

title: Missing the Mark
description: When Mark Hamill ("Famous Actor") hails a car for a lift to the Gotham City Conservatory, his driver is none other than The Joker ("Master Villain"), accompanied by Trickster ("2nd Rate Villain"). Mark is lashed to the back seat as the Joker prepares to ransom him to the studios, "who'll pay plenty to get you back!" When the police give chase, the Joker and his "witless wannabee's" argument gets heated, causing the Joker to crash the car into a thicket in the middle of the road, Swamp Thing. Whatever could make the two villains go at each other so?

title: Spring Prison Break
description: Frost reads her "How I Spent Spring Break" essay and we flashback to the tale of how Katana and Frost formed the first "Task Force X" to stop Lashina from breaking the Female Furies out of Belle Reve. During the battle between the SHH Heroes and the Furies, Barda redeems herself and joins the side of the good guys.

title: Adventure Academy: Dino Ducking
description: Prohyas and Morbidia are chosen to dodge a gauntlet of charging mechanical dinosaurs in today's lesson from Professor C, but Prohyas panics and defeats the mechanized beasts with Magiswords instead.

title: Grey Matter AW2: Lights Out!
description: A reliable power supply is vital to the Galvans' around-the-clock research, so when disaster strikes, or more specifically energy-sapping parasites, these brainy beings must have an even more reliable backup plan for keeping the lights on.

title: Stealth 101 Part 2
description: Batgirl and Ivy learn to appreciate each other's style as they fight Killer Moth.

title: Adventure Academy: Sheepy Jungle Shearing
description: Prohyas and Bimm need more than just electric clippers to sheer the constantly growing Sheepy Jungle fluff, they need Magiswords!

title: Diamondhead AW2: Great Petropian Civil War Part  2
description: The Petrosapien Civil War comes to a crucial turning point as the crystalline Petrosapiens make the hard choice to team up with their warring sub-surface cousins, the Subsapiens, to defeat the monstrous Antrosapiens that dwell near Petropia's dark planetary core.

title: Sick Day
description: Mordecai and Rigby call in sick to work so they can ride on an epic water slide.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Telly
description: Grady thinks the TV show they are watching is awful and decides to get the gang together to make their own show.

title: Uncle Grandpa's Journey
description: Quick clips of false moments from the show's hilarious past and future.

title: Car
description: Do you ever sing along to car alarms? Apple and Onion do, and pay the ultimate price!

title: Robot Rap Battle
description: Mordecai and Rigby have a rap battle with robots.

title: Dude, Where's My Invisible Jet?
description: Wonder Woman loses her invisible jet.

title: Carol
description: KO makes a documentary of a day in the life of his karate master mom, Carol.

title: Bakugan: Behind the Battle - Howlkor
description: Wynton introduces us to the three headed canine Bakugan and why he's a perfect partner to the everyone's favorite dog, Lightning.

title: Rad Cries
description: Everything Rad does, he does in an over the top amazing way, including getting emotional.

title: Keeper of the Mask
description: Vambre and Prohyas encounter the Keeper of the "Mask Magi-Sword" who challenges them to a contest.

title: Upgrade AW1: Crisis on Galvan B
description: Once devoid of natural life, Galvan B. was upgraded seemingly overnight after a Galvan terraform experiment accidentally crashed into the moon's surface. Relive the birth of the Galvanic Mechamorphs as they rise from the impact site and terraform their surroundings into the lush techno-organic moon we see today.

title: To Boulderly Go
description: Vambre & Prohyas' quest for the boulder treasure leads them to Grup the Dragon.

title: Hero of the Month: Hawkgirl
description: Hawkgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Season 3 Recap
description: From the Rubies to the Cluster, catch up on all the highlights from Steven Universe Season 3.

title: Bakugan: Beyond the Brawl - Zen and the Art of Not Brawling
description: Turtonium attempts to teach Trox and Gorthion the value of mediation but they can't help but Brawl.

title: Unboxing
description: Uncle Grandpa is making an internet video about unboxing a box.

title: Adventure Academy: Snow Decoys
description: Ghastly terrors of Transylbiria can be evaded by making snow decoys, but when Morbidia uses magic, her Abominable Snow Decoy must be destroyed by Vambre's Magiswords.

title: Bubbles' Beauty Blog But on Video
description: Bubbles' attempt to start her own beauty blog is thwarted by Blossom and Buttercup.

title: Bubbles' Beauty Blog But on Video
description: Bubbles' attempt to start her own beauty blog is thwarted by Blossom and Buttercup.

title: Cooking with Lion
description: Steven and Lion host an educational online cooking show.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 3
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: The Desolation of Grup Special
description: The Warriors are hired to "vanquish" a dragon. Includes special bonus vlogs.

title: Air Buttercup
description: Buttercup tries to show off her basketball skills in the lunchroom to no avail.

title: Rad
description: Rad shows off the ultimate power move!

title: Bakugan: Beyond the Brawl - Trox's Wild Ride
description: The Awesome Ones Bakugan try to rescue Trox who is caught on a wild ride on Lia's camera drone.

title: Fusion
description: Garnet takes over a dance studio to teach Steven about fusion!

title: Surprise
description: Harley enlists the help of Katana and Bumblebee in hiding a surprise birthday present for Batgirl in her dorm room. But when they sneak into Batgirl's dorm, they are accosted by Batgirl's booby traps.

title: Selfie Help
description: Space Cabbie is willing to write off Batman's $38,000 fare in exchange for a selfie with the super hero, to no avail. Inside Justice League headquarters, he spots Booster Gold in a Batman costume, who wants hawk his own Golden Fizz drink brand in the picture then proceeds to photobomb all of Cabbie's shots. When he stumbles into an isolated room where Wonder Woman battles a group of violent attackers, Cabbie has to decide: selfies of the fight, or help an outnumbered super hero!

title: The Blunder Games
description: As part of the Advanced Survival Skills class, Batgirl is dropped off in a remote island and must make it to the designated meeting spot before sunset. But when her equipment malfunctions, Batgirl must rely on a different set of super skills.

title: License to Fly
description: Batgirl builds her Batjet. But before she can fly, she must pass the Flyer's Exam.

title: Showdown
description: The Furies are back and this time they've stolen a very important document from Principal Waller that could have dire ramifications for Superhero High and the World! It's up to Wonder Woman and Katana to take down the Furies and save the day!

title: Designing Disaster
description: Wonder Woman finishes her super suit for Crazy Quilt's class and it's time to try it out. But the suit is a mish-mash of super hero tropes and isn't practical for saving the day. Her attempts to respond to a Save the Day drill end in disaster as her suit trips her up.

title: Dog Day After School
description: A Krytptonian is loose in Metropolis! After following the wake of school destruction, Supergirl is reunited with Krypto the Super Dog.

title: Gem Karaoke
description: Connie documents Steven and the Gems singing their hearts out to a prerecorded backing track.

title: The Origin of Frankenstein
description: Dr. Frankenstein's creation is surprisingly very intelligent until Uncle Grandpa arrives.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Weird Food
description: Puppet Gumball imagines some weird food then tries it.

title: Bubbs and Donny Get the Mail
description: Bubbles and Donny are given their most daring mission ever: get the mail.

title: Season 1 Recap
description: Catch up with this Steven Universe Season 1 recap.

title: How to Draw Beast Boy
description: Teen Titans Go! character designer Chris Battle shows you how to draw Beast Boy.

title: Justice 1, 2, 3, Go!
description: Under heavy ground fire, Batman, Wonder Woman, Plastic Man, and Cyborg search for the HIVE headquarters from their aircraft. But HIVE has cloaked its entire operation. The team splits, with Wonder Woman in Justice II and the others in tanks. An excited Plastic Man accidentally deploys the submarine instead, falling into a treetop. Wonder Woman is shot out of the sky and Batman is outmaneuvered and immobilized. It'll take a miracle to get out of HIVE's crosshairs.

title: Bakugan: Behind the Battle - Cyndeous
description: Dan introduces us and lets us why Cyndeous chose Dan to be his human partner. He also tells us why Cyndeous is a great warrior.

title: Magiswords 101: Ouch Swords
description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some that backfire.

title: Dreamium
description: Panda uses a relaxation app to help him get to sleep. But the the app's different sounds do more harm than good!

title: Hero of the Month: Lady Shiva
description: Lady Shiva is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: XLR8 AW2: Speed Round
description: The Kinecelerans live life at the fastest pace possible, even when they're letting off steam— hence their supercharged take on what we Earthlings call hockey, where every point is more electrifying than the last!

title: Separation Anxiety
description: After talking, passing notes and throwing pencils at the ceiling in class, Ms. Baker separates Clarence and Sumo. They devise ways to communicate to each other from across the room in a series of gags.

title: Franken-Ivy
description: Ivy creates a new plant pet which grows out-of-control and attacks Metropolis.

title: Steven Universe: Diamond Days Trailer
description: What's waiting for Steven and the gems when they arrive on Homeworld? Get ready for Steven Universe: Diamond Days!

title: Magiswords 101: Songs
description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some songs.

title: Birding with Guyler
description: Guyler spends a day bird watching in Bendle Park - and makes a new special friend.

title: Adventure Academy: Dragonators
description: With Gateaux wearing a dragon costume, and Vambre as a dragon-slaying knight, an exercise in dragon slaying takes a dramatic turn when Gateaux's magic turns him into a real dragon!

title: Panda's Profile Pic
description: Panda frets over not having a good photo of himself to send to a girl online. Luckily, his brothers offer their photo editing skills to help.

title: For Art's Sake
description: It's the SHH Student Art Fundraiser and the Double Dare Twins have stolen a masterpiece from the show! It's up to Katana and Supergirl to stop them and recover the painting. But when Supergirl is knocked out by kryptonite and Katana's sword is stolen, Katana must improvise and use her art supplies to defeat the Double Dare Twins.

title: Big Boy
description: In order to get them to notice he's more mature, Clarence draws chest hairs on himself and decides to show them off!

title: How to Draw K.O.
description: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes character designer, Julia Srednicki, and art director, John Pham, show you how to draw K.O.

title: Dolphinominal
description: Phil the thief swipes Prohyas' beloved Dolphin Magisword.

title: Adventure Academy: Fickle Fishing
description: Fishing for the fickle fish of the Fickle Sea is tricky. Vambre and Bimm need special bait to lure them, but when a monster fish attacks Bimm, Vambre comes to the rescue with Magiswords.

title: Bookish
description: Prohyas acts as matchmaker to a bookstore clerk who has a crush on Vambre.

title: Lion Loves to Fit in a Box
description: Lion loves to crawl into boxes, and Steven loves to film it.

title: OOOHH!!!
description: Mordecai and Rigby tour the world dong their Ooohh celebration.

title: How to Draw Enid
description: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes character designer, Julia Srednicki, and art director, John Pham, show you how to draw Enid.

title: Titans Go! Mash-Up
description: Mash-up of the best "Titans Go!"

title: Adventure Academy: Royal Tower Rescue
description: The day's lesson details the four quick steps necessary to rescue royalty from a tower, but when the rabid King Squirrel mauls poor Cattus, its up to Vambre to rescue both with her Magiswords.

title: Adventure Academy: Whack-A-Shark
description: Vambre and Phibby Croax are chosen to Whack A Shark in shark tanks, but Vambre decides that Magiswords will do better to defeat them than bops on the shark's schnozzola!

title: Attacktus
description: The Warriors are sent to the Barren Faceland to water a cactus, which grows into a giant cactus beast that attacks them.

title: Enid
description: KO breaks something near and dear to Enid!

title: Adventure Academy: Sluggernaut
description: Professor Cyrus wears a giant slug costume as Vambre and Neddy battle him on the round woody stage, but Vambre avoids a gooey brawl using Magiswords to make her the slug slayer.

title: Whose Hyas Is It Anyway?
description: The Warriors travel to futuristic Galacton and must figure out a way to get the Confusing Alien Magisword from Nohyas.

title: Bear Cleaning
description: Ice Bear vacuums the cave and accidentally rips out a patch of Grizz's fur. He tries to fix Grizz's bald spot before he notices.

title: Skyjacked
description: Under cover of night, Justice One streaks away from the Tower with Poison Ivy and Harley Quinn at the controls! The Batwing interrupts their short lived victory. Struck by one of their missiles, the Batwing starts to plummet. Batman slings a grappling hook onto Justice One and tries to get aboard, only to be launched back into the air on the craft's many separate aircraft, including a submarine. Batman gets aboard to face off with Ivy and Harley, but a smashed guidance system sends the ship plummeting. Batman buckles in. What is he doing?

title: Claw Machine
description: At the Pizza Swamp arcade, Clarence convinces passerby Vu to use his skills to free Clarence from the claw machine.

title: Stealth 101 Part 1
description: Batgirl and Ivy are partnered for Crazy Quilt's stealth suit design project.

title: Jetsetters
description: Wonder Woman is teaching Frost how to fly the Invisible Jet when Killer Moth detects them and begins to attack. Frost takes the ejector Turbo Seat to fight back. However, the jet is damaged by Killer Moth's ship, and the jet begins to plummet. The ship goes into emergency lockdown and Wonder Woman is trapped. She manages to lift the jet from the inside and crash into the bay instead of the city. Frost makes a giant ice cube that allows the jet to float and freezes Killer Moth's plane. With Killer Moth defeated, Supergirl melts the ice around Wonder Woman's jet and Batgirl restores functionality to the jet's tech. Wonder Woman emerges unscathed.

title: Phil's in the House
description: To exact his revenge on the Warriors, Phil the philanderer hides in The Warriors' house and turns the siblings against each other.

title: Magiswords 101: Zombie Pumpkin
description: Prohyas interviews Zombie Pumpkin.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Spoons
description: Frank has taken Grady's beloved house Spoon. Grady is forced into a dance off to win it back.

title: Techless Tuesday
description: Mrs. Clayface steals all of Batgirl's gadgets in an effort to break her husband out of Arkham.

title: Too Many Warriors Special
description: The Warriors and their archrivals: "Witch Way" are both hired to battle. Includes special bonus vlogs.

title: Grizzly: Ultimate Hero Champion
description: Grizz records his audition tape for his favorite athletic game show.

title: Wildside Part 2
description: With Lion-Mane subdued, Batgirl, Starfire, and Beast Boy must find all the escaped zoo animals and return them to the zoo. With the help of zoo volunteer, Mari McCabe (Vixen), they return the animals to their proper place at the zoo.

title: Bakugan: Behind the Battle - Nillious
description: Magnus tells us why he thinks his two headed Bakugan Nillious is the dangerous creature to mess with.

title: New Beginnings
description: Wonder Woman shows Supergirl around Super Hero High.

title: Fade Away Music Video
description: Beast Boy's song for Terra.

title: Crazy Quiltin
description: Wonder Woman is introduced to an important rite-of-passage for all new students at the school: creating your own iconic super hero suit. But super suit design is not Wonder Woman's forte. She brings in Katana, Bumblebee, and Harley to help her in this important task, but the results leave something to be desired.

title: All About Super Hero High
description: Wonder Woman arrives at Super Hero High. Waller introduces Bumblebee as the Ambassador to New Students. Bumblebee gives Wonder Woman the tour of Super Hero High and introduces her to some of the main Supers.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 4
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: Hero of the Month: Batgirl
description: Batgirl is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Break Time
description: Benson breakdances during a work break.

title: Hero of the Month: Bumblebee
description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Bumblebee. Waller shows a video montage of Bumblebee's exploits including saving her friends plus little comedic beats where Bumblebee changing size causes her to split a seam in her costume.

title: Stinkfly AW2: The Sweet Smell of Survival
description: For the Lepidopterrans, putting food on the family table is never as simple as running out to the grocery store. Watch as their elite Sky Soldiers go mandible-to-mandible with fearsome Tongue Beetles in what's sure to be a hunger game for the ages!

title: Tales from the Kryptomites Part 2
description: The supers must save Metropoils from the army of Kryptomites.

title: Hero of the Month: Star Sapphire
description: Star Sapphire is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 1
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: Bakugan: Behind the Battle - Pegatrix
description: Lia shares the story on how she discovered her Bakugan Pegatrix, what makes her so unique and why she's a fierce warrior.

title: Fresh Ares Part 3
description: With Catwoman's help, the supers return the amulet to Ares and save the day.

title: Spelling Bee
description: Uncle Grandpa is hosting a spelling bee game show. The contestants, Mr. Gus and Pizza Steve, are competing for the spelling bee trophy.

title: Welcome to Super Hero High
description: The school's official greeting video hosted by Principal Waller. Principal Waller introduces the school and curriculum to potential new students.

title: The Cave
description: The Bears try to get rid of a bat in their cave.

title: Fun Run
description: Pops goes on a fun run across the country.

title: Batgirl vs. Supergirl
description: Batgirl and Supergirl face off in a quest for the last piece of superfood cake.

title: Quintessential Harley
description: When Harley's web videos go viral, she deals with the unexpected consequences of fame.

title: We Are the Crystal Gems
description: Steven starts his life with the Crystal Gems in this extended version of the Steven Universe theme song.

title: Magiswords 101: Food Swords
description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some inspired by food.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup.

title: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup
description: 5 Reasons You're Actually Buttercup.

title: Fight Flub
description: Katana and Big Barda try to prove their own fighting style is the best when the Double Dare Twins attack.

title: Awesome America! Music Video
description: Robin performs a patriotic song.

title: Around Metropolis in 80 Seconds
description: Wonder Woman and Supergirl are facing off to see who's fastest, but when they keep tying, they decide to race sans superpowers. Harley hates to be left out and joins the race. As Wonder Woman and Supergirl zoom around Metropolis, they spot a bank robbery in progress and compete to see who can catch the criminals first. While they're distracted, Harley wins the race.

title: Do You Know the Muffin King?
description: The Warriors are treated to a banquet by the grateful Kotassians and Vambre accidentally eats their king.

title: Special Delivery
description: In a bad part of town, Space Cabbie primps waiting for a fare. When Booster Gold and a purple alien bug in labor fight over who gets the cab, Granny Goodness and her minions from Apokolips attack, trying to get Booster Gold. Space Cabbie heads for the hospital as the roof is torn off and Granny Goodness drops in to help with the delivery, with evil intentions for the baby alien. Now Booster Gold has to decide whether to protect the newborn and its mom or try to hitch a ride back to Earth.

title: The Goddess Must Be Crazy
description: Wonder Woman and Supergirl are in a practice mid air combat over Themyscira stadium, and Supergirl loses the round but damages the statue of a horse. Wonder Woman tells her that because of a battle between Superman and Batman, she's taken steps to keep men out of Themyscira. As they continue to train, sorcerer Felix Faust emerges from the broken statue and takes over Supergirl's body. His goal: use her to vanquish Wonder Woman and steal some tempting magical Amazonian artifacts from Themyscira.

title: Driver's Ed
description: Space Cabbie is giving a skittish Stargirl a driving lesson through an asteroid belt. "You just need to stop worrying about the things around you and focus on something ahead of you."  Her sense of justice kicks in when she spots Zilius Zox trying to break into a space ATM, and she puts her focus on him, dodging asteroids and Zox's weapons, and putting her driving skills to the test against harrowing distractions!

title: New Perry-Spective
description: Batgirl, Big Barda, and Lady Shiva set off in the Mobile HQ to wrangle Perry the Parademon. Perry playfully destroys various bits of Metropolis as the supers chase him. The supers manage to catch him and wait in anticipation, thinking Granny Goodness is behind this. However, it seems Perry has been abandoned by his previous owner, and just wants to play. Big Barda decides to keep Perry as her pet.

title: Behind the Scenes
description: A behind the scenes look at the cast and crew of Uncle Grandpa.

title: Doubles Trouble
description: Katana chooses Supergirl as her tennis doubles partner, but Supergirl's powers are too much for the game.

title: Overflow AW2: Sentries of Cascareau
description: When the Cascan Pirates aren't plundering the depths of Cascareau for buried treasure, they're depositing their spoils into savings accounts at the Fort Knox of the high seas — a bank built atop an ever-drifting island of pontoon boats, guarded by telepathic Cephalopods, its vaults impenetrable to all but the most loyal customers.

title: Flonk Stakes
description: At Ralphio's Sword Shop, the Warriors square off against an old school mate who is breaking all their beloved Magi-Swords.

title: Ring of Mire
description: Star Sapphire loses her violet lantern ring down the drain and must venture into the sewers. Ew ew ew!

title: Adventure Academy: The Thousand Eyed Stare
description: A staring contest with Blinky the Flower Boy seems simple enough, too simple, yet when Gateaux makes a spell to make the opponent more formidable, Vambre's Magiswords are needed.

title: Up and Atom
description: Wonder Woman and Batman are recruiting a reluctant Atom at his lab as a full time Justice Leaguer. "I make things little," he protests. "I'm not, like, a big fighty guy." The pitch is broken up by the explosive intrusion of Etrigan the Demon, who mops the floor with Wonder Woman and Batman when they try to send him back to the dark side. Does "little" guy Atom have enough fight in him? He'll find out once and for all if size matters!

title: Magiswords 101: Explosive Swords
description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some that pack a punch.

title: Stairways & Spiders
description: The Warriors find themselves on a long and treacherous staircase guarded by a huge talking spider.

title: Stairways & Spiders
description: The Warriors find themselves on a long and treacherous staircase guarded by a huge talking spider.

title: Adventure Academy: Trollblin Thumb Wrestling
description: Professor Cyrus' mechanical Trollblin thumb goes wonky when Bimm attempts the thumb-wresting exercise, so Prohyas uses Magiswords to pin down the rogue machine.

title: How to Draw Rad
description: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes character designer, Julia Srednicki, and art director, John Pham, show you how to draw Rad.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Pineapple
description: Gumball briefly loses his puppet mouth to an enthusiastic Pineapple.

title: Day of Fun-Ship
description: Starfire and Blackfire must protect the zoo from King Shark and realize they have more in common than they thought.

title: Something Entirely New Music Video
description: Music and lyrics by Rebecca Sugar. Additional music by Aivi Tran and Steven Velema. Performed by Erica Luttrell and Charlyne Yi.

title: Cyborg Gadgets
description: Mash-up of Cyborg's cool gadgets.

title: Greatest Villains
description: Mash-up of all the greatest TTG villians.

title: How to Draw Cyborg

description: Ben 10 character designer, Chase Standley, shows you how to draw Upgrade.

title: Something in the Hair
description: Something's odd in the JL Watchtower, Batman has released Poison Ivy from lockup and is giving her a ride home! When Plastic Man protests, one fluff of Ivy's hair releases mind control spores, which he bats away. He follows her into the garage, where she and Batman, on the Batcycle, charge across a bridge of seaweed that Ivy has created toward Metropolis. Plastic Man gives chase, dodging the Batcycle's defensive gadgets. At the docks, there's one last chance for Plastic Man to keep himself alive and break the power of Ivy's spores.

title: Waiting for Gumball: BirdPlaneBird
description: Darwin and BirdPlaneBird try to share a refreshing drink, it turns out to be hard as a puppet.

title: Magiswords 101: Grup's World
description: Grup interviews some of his friends.

title: Hands Down
description: The Warriors finally get some business doing yard work for Old Man Oldman.

title: Grey Matter AW1: The Archivists
description: Galvan Prime is home to not only the galaxy's greatest minds, but a DNA bank of every alien species in the cosmos, thus ensuring that the planet forever remains the center of DNA research for the entire universe.

title: Steven Universe Season 5 Catch-Up
description: Steven Universe fills you in on everything you need to know about Rose Quartz, the Crystal Gems, and the Diamond Authority before you dive in to new episodes! And there might just be a sneak peek of what's to come.

title: Doodle Battle
description: Clarence and his pals find a large piece of paper and have fun doodling on it.

title: Magiswords 101: Disguise Swords
description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some that change the way they look and sound.

title: Adventure Academy: Enchanted Tree Chopping
description: Enchanted dust makes a cute little tree spring to life, but Vambre feels bad chopping it down until Witchy Simone casts a spell and it grows to proper Magisword attacking size!

title: Body Electric
description: Giganta causes an electric blackout and Batgirl enlists the help of Thunder and Lightning,

title: Bodybuilding
description: Batgirl, Bumblebee and Cyborg have teamed up for the Creative Heroic Engineering Project at Superhero High. The only problem is they can't agree on anything! When Lena Luthor attacks with her new Rainbow Kryptomites our heroes will have to learn to work together to defeat her.

title: Play That Song Again
description: Vambre gets on Prohyas for playing the same song too much, and he exacts revenge.

title: Stinkfly AW1: The Silent Circle
description: The circle of life on Lepidopterra is a stinky yet harmonious effort for Lepidopterrans. The wildlife - with slime and toxic gas at their disposal - work together to maintain order on the bustling swamp planet.

title: Trading Places
description: Lena Luthor has created a power nullifying device and she is threatening to use it on Superhero High! Now, Batgirl and Supergirl will have to trade places to infiltrate Lena's lab and put the power nullifying device out of commission for good.

title: Toymano a Mano
description: A hulking robot robs Gotham City National Bank, but it's Cyborg! Toyman has a remote to control his actions. Now Batman is pitted against his own friend, who whips the Batmobile behind him till Batman stops him with a tire "boot." In rocket shoes, Toyman propels himself to the harbor and onto a rubber ducky raft, actually a controlled Plastic Man, who Batman hooks before his ally becomes a reluctant escape airplane. Now Batman needs to call on all of his genius to save his friends.

title: Seeing Red
description: A red Kryptomite, loose at Super Hero High, brings out everyone's mean side.

title: Beep Beep!
description: Lobo has big plans to earn a $100 million bounty on The Flash and "retire on the beach." He uses a distress signal to lure Superman and the Flash to a desert planet (that looks a lot like the setting for Wile E. Coyote's attempts to catch Road Runner). He puts Superman out of commission with a Kryptonite ray gun and cage. Try as Lobo does to catch "the red speedster," the Flash gets around every one of his tricks in a funny salute to the Looney Tunes classics.

title: Bakugan: Beyond the Brawl - Pranks a Lot
description: Trox pranks Gorthion, only to have the tables turn on him.

title: Power-Up!!!
description: When Rad accidentally swallows a power up that makes him do things three times, things get crazy, crazy, crazy.

title: Adventure Academy: Meatier Milking
description: Prohyas and Cattus are chosen to milk a Meatier (a one-horned cow that serves frozen yogurt from its horn), but the pair agitate the beast and Magiswords are required to calm the bull into making desert.

title: Set Me Free Music Video
description: Ballad of a cursed Bear written by Colin Heck.

title: How to Draw Raven
description: Teen Titans Go! character designer Chris Battle shows you how to draw Raven.

title: Weaponomics
description: It's demonstration day in Lucius Fox's Weaponomics class. Catwoman wields her whip. Hawkgirl swings her mace. But when Wonder Woman demonstrates her lasso, a sneaky maneuver from Cheetah causes her to lasso Mr. Fox, who spills his secrets in the lasso's grip. The incident leads to Wonder Woman getting detention!

title: Catchin' Villains Music Video
description: Beast Boy performs for Raven.

title: Goodnight Ice Bear
description: Ice Bear tries to fall asleep but the door to his fridge won't close. He tries to come up with a fix for it in any manner possible, no matter how elaborate.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 2
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: Will It Stick?

title: Adventure Academy: Barren Quicksand

description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some they absolutely need.

When she throws the Lasso of Truth around Deadshot, it turns into a limp, pink noodle with the voice of Plastic Man. Adding to the confusion, Booster Gold literally drops in holding the real lasso. An irritated Wonder Woman uses it to draw out some inconvenient truths from Booster Gold. But will she get the information she needs?

title: KO

title: 2001: A Nap Odyssey

description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some of their favorites.

description: As the premiere vacation spot of the cosmos, Arburia is not only a sandy paradise but home to the Arburian Pelarotas. Twelve excruciatingly long hours of work and school stand between the spherical species and a day at the beach spent perfecting their cannonball!

title: Bedtime
description: The girls need to get a good night's rest before family photo day, but they just can't seem to fall asleep!

Firestorm tries to help, but keeps changing the harmful green Kryptonite into other colors, red, gold, pink and black. Chided by the professor, Firestorm tries hard to remember the formula to neutralize the deadly element.

description: Learn all about the amazing swords Prohyas and Vambre use on their quests, including some of the spookiest.

description: The Warriors encounter a stoic warrior bunny whom they misinterpret as "sad" and try to cheer him up.

title: Frozen Ice
description: Grizz and Panda find Ice Bear frozen in a block of ice and attempt to save him.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Insulting Voices
description: Gumball and Darwin play with smaller hand puppets of themselves who mimic their voices very badly.

title: Pig Iron
description: Vambre & Prohyas compete for the Oinkus Magisword against Super Mighty Robot Piggeh.

With rocky exteriors capable of handling these extreme conditions, observe our fiery friends as they pass the time by perfecting their pyrokinetic powers while hanging ten on the gnarliest rivers of lava.

description: For the Fulmini, enough is just never enough. Traveling from planet to planet, draining worlds of their energy, this mighty race of conquerors must siphon energy from other planets in order to keep their own tapped-out planet spinning.

description: The Riddler stages a series of crimes in order to lure Batgirl to the rose garden where he asks her to the dance.

title: Quality Time
description: Wonder Woman explains that "bonding is important" as they unite to fight fires, explosions, and tendrils of monstrous vines that choke off the city. It's all the work of Poison Ivy and her Ivy League. Her gigantic Venus Flytrap of a vine squeezes Batman, Star Sapphire bats away Superman's attempts to catch her, Cheetah puts the Flash out of commission, and Ember makes an explosive entrance to finish him off. Wonder Woman steps in to interrupt the mayhem so the boys can get back in the game. They're all for unity, except for the Dark Knight, but the game they end up with is hardly what anyone expected.

title: Boo Yah Mash-Up
description: Mash-up of the best "Boo Yahs!"

title: Rad's Van
description: Rad shows off his rad new minivan and its rad features!

To combat the inclement weather, younglings must complete the Running of the Gauntlet, a most epic retrieval of the gliders worn on their feet. Traversing the desolate terrain at high speeds to reach the lair of a Kinet Molluscarx, the young ones must obtain the creature's precious pearl if they are to fulfill this Kineceleran rite of passage.

title: Space Worm
description: Mordecai and Rigby ride a needy space worm.

title: Zombie Reasonable
description: On their quest to find the Zombie Pumpkin Magisword, the Warriors encounter Hoppus, and fight over who saw it first.

title: It's Not About the Parts Music Video
description: Song sung by Santa to Robin.

title: Gorilla Warfare
description: The supers must save Gorilla Grodd when his former army comes to "rescue" him from SHH.

title: Eezy Freezy
description: Mr. Freeze has paralyzed Gotham City in ice and helps himself to a jewelry store's inventory. Batman catches him cold, but Mr. Freeze seems to be always two steps ahead of the hero. And Plastic Man's arrival certainly isn't going to help Batman catch Mr. Freeze, who's escaping on a motorcycle. Or will it?

title: Bakugan: Beyond the Brawl - Scorching Cold
description: Drago's cold halts a battle with Gorthion but inadvertently defeats Nillious.

description: Bakugan target practice becomes real with Nillious showing up.

description: A look at the perilous lengths to which the Tetramands must go in order to forge their formidable Warspears— the weapons that allow them to survive in such a savage wilderness.

title: Fall into Super Hero High
description: Harley Quinn reveals she made a tribute video for her friends, which they learn is a montage of them screwing up while using their powers. Their embarrassment is heightened when they learn Harley has accidentally uploaded the video and it's gone viral! Seeing the absurdity and laughing at herself, Wonder Woman breaks the girls' stunned, mortified silence. The laugh catches on. Because of Wonder Woman's leadership, all the girls who were initially embarrassed are able to laugh at themselves.

title: Hero of the Month: Katana
description: Katana is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: Clubbing
description: Principal Waller tells Poison Ivy that she needs to join a club in order to fulfill her extracurricular requirements. However, clubs are not introverted Ivy's idea of fun. Hawkgirl and Bumblebee invite Ivy to join the Junior Detective Society. Miss Martian and Starfire give Ivy the pitch for the Model United Planets. Katana and Beast Boy want her for Band Club. But then, the glimmering test tubes of Science Club catch Ivy's eye. Ivy adds her name to the sign-up sheet manned by Frost and Flash. Later, during the first Science Club meeting, Ivy shows off her modified plants, which creates chaos for Star Sapphire. Ivy grins. Clubs are fun!

title: Nom Nom vs. Hamster
description: Nom Nom is forced to share the spotlight on his new video with an uncooperative hamster.

title: Magiswords 101: Vambre's Reviews
description: Vambre reviews her favorite books while demonstrating swords.

description: Gumball and Darwin discover smaller hand puppet  versions of themselves and get caught in an infinite loop of puppets.

title: Chemistry

But while she's waiting, flirty Firestorm would like nothing more than to impress her by shouting nerdy terms, coached by Prof. Martin Stein ("Keynesian economics, Hegelian dialecticism!") which makes her yawn. As she fends off HIVE's violent attack, Firestorm throws out theory after theory, but it's not helping much. Will he be able to use his own powers and dazzle her at the same time?

Green Arrow gets rid of his loudmouth friend, who returns as a fire hydrant, a rat, and a cat to get closer to the Penguin's HQ. He finds the villain and his thugs, so he delivers himself to their door as a pizza. Inside, it's time to show what he can do against the Penguin and his minions. Now, where's Green Arrow?

title: Adventure Academy: Oasis of Fear
description: In a lesson of survival, Phibby and Prohyas are instructed to create an "Oasis Of Fear" to frighten menacing desert night creatures, but Prohyas scares them away with Magiswords instead.

description: KO's inner monologue tells us how even a mundane everyday activity is another step in his journey to being a great hero.

title: Mint Condition
description: Cyborg has good news and bad. Good: he's added lots of new action figures to his collectible toys. Bad: Toyman has turned all the "Bot-Bots," which he's been collecting since childhood, into weapons. In the ensuing battle, a hysterical Cyborg needs to choose whether he's willing to destroy or damage his precious mint condition collectibles, or be a victim of their destruction. Will he stop the battle before they lose all their value, or will he allow Toyman, and his new toy army, to destroy Justice League's headquarters?

title: Wildvine AW1: Wild Siders
description: Flors Verdana, green with vegetation, is as wild and abundant as the Florauna that inhabit it. Let's take a walk on the wild side as the plant-based aliens trade admiring the planet's lush beauty for the dangerous thrill of waking a sleeping giant.

title: Saving the Day
description: It's time for Wonder Woman to reveal her new super suit for Crazy Quilt's final grade. Bumblebee, Harley and Ivy watch from the sidelines in support of their friend. Wonder Woman steps onto the catwalk and reveals her new outfit. But before Crazy Quilt announces Wonder Woman's grade, the Save the Day alarm buzzes! Wearing her new costume, Wonder Woman leads Bumble Bee, Harley, and Ivy on a mission to save the day! They must save Mr. Fox who's stuck on top of the Amethyst! The girls save their teacher, but in the process, Wonder Woman discovers that Cheetah was behind this malicious deed. In the grip of Wonder Woman's lasso, Cheetah confesses all her crimes.

title: Cannonbolt AW2: When Mega-Sharks Attack!
description: Arburia is well-known across the galaxy for its beach season but this year's interplanetary vacationers won't be catching many waves if the Pelarotas can't rid their waters of an unwanted visitor: the Carcharadon, a billion-toothed beast that makes Jaws look like canned tuna!

title: Log Ride
description: The Bears become obsessed with taking the perfect "action shot" picture on a log ride at an amusement park. They go on the ride over and over again until they've got the best shot.

title: Ninja Shoes
description: Mordecai and Rigby try to sneak out of the house wearing ninja shoes.

title: Fresh Ares Part 2
description: As Ares reigns destruction on Metropolis, the supers must recover the amulet.

title: The 1973 Tetherball Championship Trophy
description: Mordecai and Rigby compete to win a vintage tetherball championship trophy.

title: Bounce House
description: A kid's party is almost ruined, until UG arrives with his special Bounce House.

title: Blissfully Unaware
description: Bliss uses her telekinetic powers to help the Professor make a more delicious dinner.

description: Mad Harriet has stolen Batgirl's Batjet and she's threatening Superhero High with it. Batgirl, Wonder Woman, Supergirl and Harley Quinn have to stop her. But as dangerous as Mad Harriet being on the loose is will Harley Quinn's help be even worse?

description: The Awesome Ones Bakugan must use their Special Abilities to get Lupitheon to get a much needed shower.

description: Dan introduces us to his number one Bakugan Drago, showcasing what makes him potentially the most powerful Bakugan ever.

description: Nillious, Artulean and Maxotaur are going to ambush Drago but wind up getting into a Bakugan Brawl between themselves.

description: Uncle Grandpa discovers a box of lost Uncle Grandpa episodes. The gang decides to watch the video reel.

title: Plastic Man of Steel
description: Lois Lane believes that Clark Kent is Superman, so the Man of Steel enlists Plastic Man to put the doubt back by having him pose as Clark. Lois lures "Clark" to the Daily Planet rooftop and jumps to test him, but she's rescued by, Superman!  But he's hit with red Sun radiation beamed by an armored Lex Luthor, who wants a retraction of Lois's "lies" about him in the paper. The weakened Superman is no match for Luthor in (body armor), so Plastic Man has to stretch to the occasion.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Beards
description: Puppet Gumball and Darwin discover they can grow very weird beards.

title: Hero of the Month: Harley Quinn
description: Harley Quinn is anointed Hero of the Month.

title: The Land Before Slime
description: Vambre & Prohyas head to the Dinosaur Kingdom to recover a lost baby dinosaur.

title: Hero of the Month: Wonder Woman
description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M is Wonder Woman. Waller shows a video montage of Wonder Woman's exploits, which is mix of big heroic moments, and the small beats of friendship, laughter and fun. Wonder Woman's heroism isn't just about superpowers, but also about the amazing, caring person she is.

title: Enid vs. Rad
description: Enid and Rad both think the other one has it easy, and they switch jobs to prove it.

title: Hero of the Month: Poison Ivy
description: Principal Waller makes her monthly announcement where she anoints a student as the Hero of the Month. This month, the H.O.M. is Poison Ivy. Waller shows a video montage of Poison Ivy's exploits as Ivy saves the students from the grip of her out-of-control plants.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Grump
description: Frank is getting grumpy waiting for Gumball and Darwin to return so Grady and Howdy throw a party to cheer him up.

description: Vambre can't get her brain to go to sleep and it takes control of her body.

description: Lia let's us know about Gorthian the Bakugan special abilities and beyond his strength why she loves brawling with him on her side.

title: Clown Party
description: The Joker and Batman duke it out on a Gotham City rooftop. In their between punch banter, Batman calls the Joker's jokes, "old, but never funny." The villain takes offense and drops a pair of gas bombs, then escapes the explosion with a jet pack, which gets taken down with a Batarang. He falls, spiraling right into a little kid's backyard birthday party. Now, the Joker gets to show off his comic timing with what he's always wanted, a captive audience!

title: Beans
description: Clarence attempts to wake a sleeping dog.

title: Adventure Academy: Ham of Glory
description: Phibby Croax wants to fight in the extreme and has no patience to learn the ham-fisted fighting style in the day's lesson called, the Ham Of Glory, so Prohyas breaks out Magiswords to teach Phibby not to be a meathead.

description: Pizza Steve has the crew do his bidding for fear of being transformed by his mind powers.

title: Beauford T. Pusser
description: Inspired by the short Every Child, an oprhan ktten is passed from kid to kid until it finally makes its way to Ms. Baker, who names him Beauford T. Pusser.

title: Unboxing
